ToroidZip
=========

A ratio-first compression codec for smooth floating-point data.

Encodes float64 sequences as ratios (x[n] / x[n-1]) rather than absolute
values. Ratio distributions in smooth data are tightly clustered around 1.0
(the Identity state), yielding a better entropy model than value-based codecs.
Boundary events (near-zero or extreme ratios) are handled as a separate class
rather than disrupting the main distribution.

Theoretical basis: Toroidal Arithmetic — a ratio-first number system where 0
and ∞ are boundary poles rather than algebraic values, and identity (x/x=1)
is treated as a higher-order law than value equality.

Status: Milestone 7 complete — tiered adaptive fallback (v5 stream, ClassNormal32);
u32 middle tier between uint16 and float64 fully shipped and benchmarked.
Milestone 8 next — formalization, algorithm writeup, white paper.

Usage
-----

  go install github.com/Destraag/toroidzip/cmd/toroidzip@latest

  # Lossless encode/decode (rANS entropy coding)
  toroidzip encode input.f64 output.tzrz
  toroidzip decode input.tzrz output.f64

  # Quantized (lossy) encode — 8 sig-fig precision
  toroidzip encode --lossy --sig-figs 8 input.f64 output.tzrz

  # Auto-select entropy mode from data
  toroidzip encode --auto input.f64 output.tzrz

  # Analyze data before encoding (precision, drift, lossless viability, tier preview)
  toroidzip analyze input.f64
  # Output includes: recommended precision (tier-ceiling bumped), identity
  # fraction with lossless viability warning, drift mode speed tradeoff note.

  # Adaptive tier preview — show % u16 / u32 / float64 at a given tolerance
  toroidzip analyze --tolerance 1e-6 input.f64
  toroidzip analyze --sig-figs 6 input.f64

Input/output: raw IEEE 754 little-endian float64 binary files.

Flags (encode)
--------------

  --entropy-mode raw|lossless|quantized|adaptive
      raw:       no entropy coding (stream v1, baseline)
      lossless:  rANS-coded ratio stream (stream v2, default)
      quantized: lossy N-bit log-space quantization (stream v3)
      adaptive:  per-ratio tiered hybrid — u16 / u32 / float64 (stream v5)
                 tier chosen per ratio so ε is satisfied with minimum bytes

  --tolerance T          max relative error per ratio (adaptive mode only)
  --sig-figs N           significant decimal figures to retain (1–9); implies quantized
                         when used with --entropy-mode adaptive: sets both bits and ε
  --precision N          precision bits for quantized (1–30) or adaptive u16 tier (1–16)
  --auto                 auto-select entropy mode by analyzing the input
  --lossy                shorthand for --entropy-mode quantized
  --drift-mode A|B       A = periodic reanchor (default), B = Kahan compensate
  --reanchor-interval N  values between verbatim anchors (default 256)

Flags (analyze)
---------------

  --tolerance T    show adaptive tier preview at this ε
  --sig-figs N     show adaptive tier preview for N sig figs
  --precision N    u16 precision bits for tier preview (default: recommended bits)

Structure
---------

  codec/          encode/decode logic, boundary classification, rANS, quantization
  codec/analyze.go  AnalyzeDrift, AnalyzePrecision, ExtractNormalRatios, AnalyzeTiers
  cmd/toroidzip/  CLI binary (encode, decode, analyze subcommands)
  scripts/        bench_m4.sh — external baseline benchmark vs zstd/brotli/fpzip
                    usage: ./scripts/bench_m4.sh [--n N] [--effort fast|best|both]
                                                  [--sig-figs N] [--adaptive] [--keep]
                  gen_datasets/ — synthetic .f64 dataset generator
  PLAN            algorithm design and session log
  ROADMAP         milestone tracker

